item.title: Model-Predictive Control
item.description: This code uses CVXPY as an optimization modeling tool Vehicle model linearization Vehicle model is $ \dot{x} = vcos(\phi)$ $$ \dot{y} = vsin((\phi)$$ $$ \dot{v} = a$$ $$ \dot{\phi} = \frac{vtan(\delta)}{L}$$ State and Input vector: $$ z = [x, y, v,\phi] $$ $$u = [a, \delta]$$ x: x-position; y:y-position; v:velocity; φ: yaw angle; a: accellation; δ: steering angle ODE is $$ \dot{z} =\frac{\partial }{\partial z} z = f(z, u) = A’z+B’u$$
